ygData.subject: Re: Gigantic Cracked Tusk
ygData.msgSnippet: No, however i was recently in SK when a person was auctioning to by a elephant tusk.. he said it was a rare tusk, unlike the normal Mammoth tusks, and small
ygData.messageBody:
No, however i was recently in SK when a person was auctioning to by a elephant tusk.. he said it was a rare tusk, unlike the normal Mammoth tusks, and small mammoth tusks that are normally found on elephants and mammoths..
He said he wanted it for his dark elf friend, who needed it for a quest of some sort.. thats all the info i got out of him.

Wes Lobdell,
Quote: +ACI-The certain proof that intelligent life exists elsewhere in the universe
is that no one has bothered to make contact with us.+ACI-
